{
  "texts": [
    "As a model system, consider a pair of spinless weakly dispersive bands, one each in valley τ = ±1.",
    "These bands have Chern numbers Cτ (where C is an integer), and are interchanged by time-reversal symmetry.",
    "We wish to construct a mean-field insulating state at filling ν = 1.",
    "Evidently, one option is to spontaneously break time reversal and valley polarize, resulting a state with a net Chern number.",
    "Now, imagine tuning the bandwidth or the competition between inter-and intravalley-interactions to destabilize this in favor of a state with non-zero IVC."
  ]
}